      = \n}}\n\nThe '''Great Britain men's national water polo team''' is the representative for [[Great Britain]] in international men's [[water polo]]. The team has participated in eleven tournaments at the [[Summer Olympics]]. The dominant team in the sport in the early twentieth century, with four Olympic titles. The only major competition they have ever qualified for was the first world championships in 1973 . They qualified for the [[London 2012 Olympics]] by virtue of their representing the host country.\n\n==Results==\n\n===Olympic Games===\n{{div col}}\n*[[Water polo at the 1900 Summer Olympics|1900]] \u2014 '''{{gold1}} Gold medal'''<ref name=\"HistoFINA PDF\">{{cite web|title=HistoFINA \u2013 Water polo medalists and statistics \u2013 Download |url=https://www.fina.org/sites/default/files/histofina_wp_2018_final_0.pdf |website=fina.org |publisher=[[FINA]] |date=September 2017 |format=PDF |pages=5, 15 |access-date=30 March 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190528143003/https://www.fina.org/sites/default/files/histofina_wp_2018_final_0.pdf |archive-date=28 May 2019 }}</ref>\n*[[Water polo at the 1908 Summer Olympics|1908]] \u2014 '''{{gold1}} Gold medal'''\n*[[Water polo at the 1912 Summer Olympics|1912]] \u2014 '''{{gold1}} Gold medal'''\n*[[Water polo at the 1920 Summer Olympics|1920]] \u2014 '''{{gold1}} Gold medal'''\n*[[Water polo at the 1924 Summer Olympics|1924]] \u2014 1st round (8th place)\n*[[Water polo at the 1928 Summer Olympics|1928]] \u2014 4th place\n*[[Water polo at the 1936 Summer Olympics|1936]] \u2014 8th place\n*[[Water polo at the 1948 Summer Olympics|1948]] \u2014 First round (13th place)\n*[[Water polo at the 1952 Summer Olympics|1952]] \u2014 Second round (12th place)\n*[[Water polo at the 1956 Summer Olympics|1956]] \u2014 7th place\n*[[Water polo at the 2012 Summer Olympics|2012]] \u2014 12th place\n{{div col end}}\n\n===World Championship===\n*[[Water polo at the 1973 World Aquatics Championships \u2013 Men's tournament|1973]] &mdash; 15th place<ref name=\"HistoFINA PDF\"/>\n\n==Current roster==\n{{2012 Summer Olympics Great Britain men's water polo team roster}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Great Britain squads\n|bg = #012169\n|fg = #FFFFFF\n|bordercolor = #C8102E\n|list1 = \n{{Great Britain men's water polo squad 1900 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Great Britain men's water polo squad 1908 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Great Britain men's water polo squad 1912 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Great Britain men's water polo squad 1920 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Great Britain men's water polo squad 1924 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Great Britain men's water polo squad 1928 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Great Britain men's water polo squad 1936 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Great Britain men's water polo squad 2012 Summer Olympics}}\n}}\n{{LEN Water polo national teams}}\n{{Summer Olympics Men's Water polo tournament winners}}\n\n[[Category:Men's national sports teams of the United Kingdom|Water polo]]\n[[Category:Men's national water polo teams]]\n[[Category:Great Britain national water polo team| ]]\n", "name_user": "Phikia", "label": "safe", "comment": "{{Infobox national water polo team}} parameters", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Great_Britain_men%27s_national_water_polo_team"}
{"title_page": "1964 Trentino-Alto Adige/S\u00fcdtirol regional election", "text_new": "{{politics of Trentino-AA/ST}}\n\nThe '''Trentino-Alto Adige/S\u00fcdtirol regional election of 1964''' took place on 15 November 1964.\n\nFollowing inter-etnic tensions with the [[German]] minority, the [[Christian Democracy]] formed an [[organic Centre-left]] majority with the [[Democratic Socialist]]s and the [[Socialist]]s, joined by the [[FP\u00d6]]-sister party [[Tyrolean Homeland Party|THP]].\n\n==Results==\n===Regional Council===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%; text-align:right;\"\n|-\n! colspan=2|Party\n! votes\n! votes (%)\n! seats\n|-\n| bgcolor=White| \n|align=left| [[Christian Democracy (Italy)|Christian Democracy]]\n| 168,088\n| 36.6\n| 19\n|-\n| bgcolor=Gray| \n|align=left| [[South Tyrolean People's Party]]\n| 134,188\n| 29.3\n| 16\n|-\n| bgcolor=Hotpink | \n|align=left| [[Italian Socialist Party]]\n| 37,496\n| 8.2\n| 4\n|-\n| bgcolor=Pink| \n|align=left| [[Italian Democratic Socialist Party]]\n| 27,534\n| 6.0\n| 3\n|-\n| bgcolor=Red| \n|align=left| [[Italian Communist Party]]\n| 20,747\n| 4.5\n| 2\n|-\n| bgcolor=Black| \n|align=left| [[Italian Social Movement]]\n| 18,240\n| 4.0\n| 2\n|-\n| bgcolor=Blue| \n|align=left| [[Italian Liberal Party]]\n| 17,775\n| 3.9\n| 2\n|-\n| bgcolor=Gray| \n|align=left| [[Trentino Tyrolean People's Party]]\n| 13,756\n| 3.0\n| 2\n|-\n| bgcolor=Cyan| \n|align=left| [[Craftsman-Farmer Alliance]]\n| 6,307\n| 1.4\n| 1\n|-\n|\n|align=left| [[Italian Socialist Party of Proletarian Unity]]\n| 6,079\n| 1.3\n| -\n|-\n| bgcolor=Maroon|\n|align=left| [[Tyrolean Homeland Party]]\n| 5,258\n| 1.2\n| 1\n|-\n|\n|align=left| Others\n| 3,245\n| 0.7\n| -\n|- bgcolor=\"EFEFEF\"\n|align=left colspan=2| '''Total'''\n| '''458,713'''\n| '''100.0'''\n| '''52'''\n|-\n!colspan=5| [[File:TrentinoAA Council 1964.svg|400px]]\n|}\n<small>Source: [http://www.regione.taa.it/Elettorale/risultati/reg_1998.pdf Trentino-Alto Adige/S\u00fcdtirol Region]</sm