{"title_page": "Marcia Pally", "text_new": "\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Marcia Pally\n| image =Marcia Pally press photo.jpg\n| alt = Marcia Pally in her Office\n| caption =Marcia Pally\n| birth_name =\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1951|03|1}}\n| birth_place =New York\n| death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place =\n| nationality =American\n| other_names =\n| parents      = Sidney Pally <br> Nettie Rose Pally\n| relatives    = Iona M. Pally (b. Nov. 28, 1955) (sister)\n| occupation = Professor, Author\n| years_active =\n| known_for =\n| notable_works =Commonwealth and Covenant: Economics, Politics, and Theologies of Relationality / The New Evangelicals: Expanding the Vision of the Common Good\n}}\n\n'''Marcia Deborah Pally''' (born March 1, 1951) is a professor at the [[New York University]] [[Steinhardt School of Culture, Education, and Human Development]] <ref>[https://www.nyu.edu/search.html?search=marcia%20pally&st=people NYU Faculty]</ref>. \n\n==Early life and education==\nMarcia Pally was born in New York on March 1, 1951, one of two daughters of Dr. Sidney Pally (1921-1997), a psychologist with the Veterans Administration,<ref>[https://aad.archives.gov/aad/display-partial-records.jsp?f=4472&mtch=1&q=Pally&cat=all&dt=2158&tf=F National Archives]</ref> <ref>[https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.1467-6494.1955.tb01161.x Article by Dr. Sidney Pally]</ref> and Nettie Rose Pally (n\u00e9e Schachter) (1921-2001). At the time of her birth, Pally's father was completing his [[Doctor of Philosophy | Ph.D.]] at the [[University of Pennsylvania]].\n\nPally was raised in [[Elmhurst, Queens]]. She received her early education at the Solomon Schechter School of Queens,<ref>[https://www.sssq.org/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=1025987&type=d&pREC_ID=1331905 SSSQ Alumni Newsletter]</ref> and has expressed her thanks to her teachers at that school in the \"Acknowledgments\" of several of her books.<ref> See, e.g., Sex & Sensibility, p. iv; The New Evangelicals, p. xx;  Commonwealth and Covenant, p. viii. </ref> Pally completed her high school education at Forest Hills High School,<ref>[http://www.e-yearbook.com/yearbooks/Forest_Hills_High_School_Forester_Yearbook/1968/Page_97.html Forest Hills High School Yearbook]</ref> and the Ivry Prozdor High School <ref>[http://www.jtsa.edu/prozdor-teen-learning Prozdor High School]</ref> of the [[Jewish Theological Seminary of America]]. She earned a [[Bachelor of Science| B.Sc.]] in [[Human Ecology]] from [[Cornell University]] in 1971,<ref> [https://cdsun.library.cornell.edu/cgi-bin/cornell?a=d&d=CDS19710604.1.10 Cornell Sun]</ref> and an [[Master of Fine Arts| M.F.A.]] in choreography <ref>[https://www.wacd.ucla.edu/programs/graduate/choreographic-inquiry UCLA Programs]</ref> from the [[University of California, Los Angeles]].<ref>[https://www.wiko-berlin.de/fellows/fellowfinder/detail/2006-pally-marcia Marcia Pally at Wissenschaftskolleg zu Berliun]</ref> <ref>[https://www.sssq.org/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=1025987&type=d&pREC_ID=1331905 SSSQ Alumni Newsletter]</ref> In 1995, Pally earned a doctorate [[Doctor of Education|(Ed.D.)]] from [[New York University]].<ref>[https://marciapally.com/prof-dr-marcia-pally-c-v/ Marcia Pally CV]</ref>\n\n==Early career==\nFollowing her career as a dancer and choreographer,<ref>https://www.wiko-berlin.de/fileadmin/Jahrbuchberichte/2006/2006_07_Pally_Marcia_Jahrbuchbericht.pdf</ref><ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1979/11/30/archives/events-and-openings-friday-film-music-dance-cabaret-saturday.html Mel Wong Dance Company - New York Times]</ref><ref>[https://www.ejumpcut.org/archive/onlinessays/JC24-25folder/LesbianFilmography.html ''In the Pictures'', Ithaca Video Project, video documentary about lesbian choreographer Marcia Pally in Jump Cut: A Review of Contemporary Media, issue 24/25, p. 90 (March 1981)]</ref> Pally worked as a columnist, and a dance and film critic<ref>[https://www.filmcomment.com/article/willing-sinner-pedro-almodovar/ Marcia Pally in ''Film Comment'']</ref> in Europe<ref>[https://www.arsenal-berlin.de/forumarchiv/forum97/awards.html FIPRESCI jury members]</ref> and the United States,<ref>[https://archive.org/stream/wbaifolioaugsep94wbairich/wbaifolioaugsep94wbairich_djvu.txt Marcia Pally and [[Stuart Klawans]] at WBAI radio]</ref> and as a prominent activist for gay and lesbian rights,<ref>[https://variety.com/2006/scene/markets-festivals/from-rags-to-rich-kudos-1117941139/ Marcia Pally, dance critic for the Native at GLAAD rally, Variety (April 6, 2006)]</ref><ref> Marcia Pally, ''AIDS and the Politics of Despair: Lighting Our Own Funeral Pyre'', The Advocate, issue 436 (Dec. 24, 1985)</ref> and an advocate for women's rights and [[freedom of speech | freedom of expression]].<ref>[https://archive.org/details/isbn_9780415918220/page/256/mode/2up/search/Pally Joan Kennedy Taylor, \"Feminists for Free Expression\" in Jill Nagle (ed.), ''Whores and Other Feminists'', p. 256 (1997)]</ref>\n\nIn 1983, Marcia Pally worked with [[Vito Russo]] in producing<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1197781/ Marcia Pally at IMDB]</ref><ref>[https://archive.org/details/outinalldirectio00witt/page/118/mode/2up/search/Marcia+Pally?q=GLAAD+%22Marcia+Pally%22 Lynn Witt, Sherry Thomas & Eric Marcus (eds.), Out in All Directions, p. 118 (1995)]</ref> and co-hosting ''Our Time'', a groundbreaking television series focused on the gay and lesbian community. The show ran for thirteen episodes on public television station [[WNYC]].<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_O5Vwyj4OOg Marcia Pally co-hosting ''Our Time'', episode 4]</ref> <ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nRFKBuKBGzo Marcia Pally co-hosting ''Our Time'', episode 5]</ref> \n\nIn 1985, Pally became one of the founders,<ref>[https://archive.org/details/alternatechannel00stev/page/254/mode/2up/search/Marcia+Pally?q=GLAAD+%22Marcia+Pally%22 Steven Capsuto, Alternate Channels, p. 254 (2000)]</ref><ref>[https://archive.org/details/longroadtofreedo0000unse/page/290/mode/2up/search/Marcia+Pally?q=GLAAD+%22Marcia+Pally%22 Mark Thompson (ed.), Long Road to Freedom, p. 290 (1994)]</ref> and original board members of [[GLAAD]], the Gay & Lesbian Alliance Against Defamation, an organization formed to protest against homophobic coverage of AIDS in the media,<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ri3Utl8DpFc Marcia Pally representing the Gay & Lesbian Alliance (at 0:52)]</ref> and served as acting chair. Pally's tenure as acting chair was contentious, and led to the resignation of several board members, as well as to criticism of Pally's \"supposed foray into heterosexuality\", and as an assertion that she was unsuitable to hold a position of leadership in the organization due to her alleged refusal to identify as a lesbian. Pally categorically denied the allegations, describing them as \"ludicrous\"<ref>[https://archive.org/details/gaycommunitynews1432gayc/page/2/mode/2up/''Politics or Ego: GLAAD Saga Unravelled'', Gay Community News, p. 3 (March 1-7, 1987)]</ref> Nevertheless, over the course of the 1990s and thereafter, Pally pursued a number of heterosexual relationships, including an aborted engagement in 2003 that was the cause of controversy in New York's [[Ansche Chesed]] congregation, when Pally demanded and was refused an ''[[aufruf]]'' for her non-Jewish fianc\u00e9.\n\nIn 1992, Pally founded the advocacy group Feminists for Free Expression,<ref>[https://www.boell-bw.de/fileadmin/Heinrich-Boell-Stiftung/2004/04-07BioPally.pdf Marcia Pally bio at Heinrich Boell Stiftung]</ref> <ref> [https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/pdf/10.1002/9781118896877.wbiehs370 Patti Britton, ''Pornography: female directors'']</ref> and served as president of the organization.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1994/07/24/opinion/l-no-censors-needed-on-the-data-highway-758990.html OpEd by Marcia Pally, President FFE, New York Times]</ref> <ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1994/12/11/style/coming-in-from-the-cold-a-fur-lovers-backlash.html Marcia Pally, New York Times]</ref> During that period, Pally published two books on censorship: ''Sense and Censorship: The Vanity of the Bonfires'', and ''Sex & Sensibility: Reflections on Forbidden Mirrors and the Will to Censor''.<ref>[https://archive.org/details/sexsensibilityre00pall?q=%22marcia+pally%22 ''Sex & Sensibility: Reflections on Forbidden Mirrors and the Will to Censor'']</ref>\n\nAfter earning a doctorate [[Doctor of Education|(Ed.D.)]] from [[New York University]]<ref>[https://marciapally.com/prof-dr-marcia-pally-c-v/ Marcia Pally c.v.]</ref> in 1995, Pally embarked upon an academic career.\n\n==Academic Career ==\nProfessor '''Marcia Pally''' teaches at New York University (adjunct),<ref>[http://nyihumanities.org/marcia-pally/ Marcia Pally at New York University]</ref> at Fordham University,<ref>[https://411.fordham.edu/detail.jsp?id=pally Marcia Pally at Fordham University]</ref> and is a regular guest professor at the Theology Faculty of Humboldt University zu Berlin.<ref>[https://www.theologie.hu-berlin.de/de/fakultaet/personen/mitarbeiter/1686853 Marcia Pally at the Theology Faculty of Humboldt University zu Berlin]</ref> Her most recent books are ''Commonwealth and Covenant: Economics, Politics, and Theologies of Relationality'' (Eerdmans, 2016)<ref>[https://www.eerdmans.com/Products/7104/commonwealth-and-covenant.aspx Commonwealth and Covenant: Economics, Politics, and Theologies of Relationality (Eerdmans, 2016)]</ref> and ''The New Evangelicals: Expanding the Vision of the Common Good''<ref>[https://www.eerdmans.com/Products/6640/the-new-evangelicals.aspx The New Evangelicals: Expanding the Vision of the Common Good]</ref> (in German: ''Die neuen Evangelikalen: Freiheitsgewinne durch fromme Politik'').<ref>[https://www.amazon.de/Die-Neuen-Evangelikalen-den-Freiheitsgewinne/dp/3940432938 (Eerdmans, 2011; in German: Die neuen Evangelikalen: Freiheitsgewinne durch fromme Politik, Berlin University Press, 2010)]</ref>. \n\n''Commonwealth and Covenant'' has been selected by the United Nations Committee on Education for Justice \u201cto be distributed in their materials to \u201ceducators, academics, policy-makers, parents, students, teacher training institutes, and curriculum developers throughout the world\u201d and it was nominated for a Grawemeyer Award in religion. \n\nPally's research interests include religion, culture, and politics as well as the intersection of language and culture. During the 1990s, she wrote in critique of government censorship in such works as ''Sense and Censorship'', <ref>https://www.amazon.com/Sense-censorship-bonfires-Marcia-Pally/dp/B0006EZF3M</ref> and ''Sex & Sensibility: Reflections on Forbidden Mirrors and the Will to Censor''<ref>https://www.amazon.com/Sex-Sensibility-Reflections-Forbidden-Mirrors/dp/0880013648</ref> but has stepped away from legal questions in recent years. \n\nPally spoke at the World Economic Forum<ref>[https://www.weforum.org/agenda/2009/12/does-religions-claim-to-truth-lead-to-violence/ Marcia Pally at the World Economic Forum]</ref> in 2010 and has been awarded the prestigious Mercator Guest Professorship (German Research Foundation)<ref>[https://berkleycenter.georgetown.edu/people/marcia-pally Marcia Pally at the Mercator Guest Professorship (German Research Foundation)]</ref> as well as grants from the German Academic Exchange Service, from the Fritz Thyssen Foundation and the Telos/Paul Piccone Institute. In addition, she is the co-recipient of a German Research Foundation grant to compare the political ethics and activism of American and German evangelicals, the only study of its kind.\n\nIn 2007 and 2010, she was a Fellow at the Institute for Advanced Study in Berlin (Wissenschaftskolleg zu Berlin).<ref>[https://www.wiko-berlin.de/fellows/fellowfinder/detail/2006-pally-marcia/ Marcia Pally at the Institute for Advanced Study in Berlin (Wissenschaftskolleg zu Berlin)]</ref>\n\n== Author ==\nIn addition to her academic work, Prof. Pally has been a columnist in the U.S. and Europe for over 30 years, writing for Religion and Ethics, <ref>https://www.abc.net.au/religion/redeeming-populism-the-promise-of-a-liberal-covenanted-republic/10094760</ref> Commonweal,<ref>[https://www.commonwealmagazine.org/-invention-antichrist Marcia Pally at Commonweal]</ref> and Religion News Service,<ref>[http://religionnews.com/author/marciapally/ Marcia Pally at Religion News Service]</ref>  among other periodicals. She has published one opinion piece in The New York Times,<ref>[https://campaignstops.blogs.nytimes.com/author/marcia-pally/ ''The New Evangelicals'', The New York Times (Dec. 9, 2011)]</ref>, and one in The Washington Post,<ref>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/opinions/1992/02/11/porn-didnt-make-him-do-it/e5535a7c-b405-42a4-b595-364cf16fa87f/ ''Porn Didn't Make Him Do It'', Washington Post (February 11, 1992) at A21]</ref> two comments in The Guardian,<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/profile/marcia-pally Marcia Pally at The Guardian]</ref> and columns in Internationale Politik (German Council on Foreign Relations),<ref>[http://www.ipg-journal.de/ipg/autorinnen-und-autoren/autor/ipg-author/detail/Author/marcia-pally/ Marcia Pally at Internationale Politik (German Council on Foreign Relations)]</ref> [[Foreign Policy]],<ref>[https://foreignpolicy.com/2006/11/08/a-familiar-foreign-policy/ Marcia Pally in Foreign Policy]</ref> Die Zeit,<ref>[http://www.zeit.de/autoren/P/Marcia_Pally Marcia Pally at Die Zeit]</ref> Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung, S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung, Tageszeitung,<ref>[https://www.taz.de/!a=Marcia+Pally/ Marcia Pally at Tageszeitung]</ref> Berliner Zeitung,<ref>[http://www.berliner-zeitung.de/action/berliner-zeitung/4484314/search?query=marcia+pally Marcia Pally at Berliner Zeitung]</ref> Frankfurter Rundschau,<ref>[http://www.fr.de/Marcia+Pally~/ Marcia Pally at Frankfurter Rundschau]</ref> Penthouse,<ref> [https://archive.org/details/penthousejuly1996/page/n19/mode/2up/search/+Pally?q=%22MArcia+Pally%22 Marcia Pally,''Film'', Penthouse, p.19 (July 1996)] </ref> [[The Advocate (LGBT magazine)|The Advocate]],<ref>[https://www.biblio.com/book/advocate-issue-429-september-17-1985/d/904100733 ''Lesbian Perspectives (Part Five of Five) - Sorrow and Silk Stockings: The Woeful State of Femme'', The Advocate: The National Gay Newsmagazine (Issue No. 429, September 17, 1985)]</ref> The [[New York Native]],<ref>[https://digital.lib.uh.edu/collection/montrose/item/8226 Gay Press Association Excellence in Editorial and Commentary award to Marcia Pally for \"Fireworks at the Women's Sexuality Conference\" in The New York Native]</ref> [[The Village Voice]],<ref> [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Illusions_(1982_film)#Critical_reception Critical Reception of \"Illusions\"] </ref> [[The Nation]],<ref>[https://www.questia.com/magazine/1G1-3833131/ban-sexism-not-pornography Marcia Pally, Ban Sexism, Not Pornography]</ref> and Vanity Fair, <ref>[https://archive.vanityfair.com/article/1990/12/charles-in-charge Marcia Pally in Vanity Fair]</ref> among other publications.\n\nMarcia Pally has given lectures at many universities and professional associations, among them Oxford, The University of Chicago, Harvard, Columbia University, Telos Institute, Humboldt University (Berlin), The Free University-Berlin, The University of Zurich, Eidgen\u00f6ssische Technische Hochschule, Ruhr University-Bochum, Bielefeld University, The Cato Institute, the Aspen Institute-Berlin.\n\nIn the field of language acquisition, Pally was the editor of ''Sustained Content-Based Teaching in Academic ESL/EFL'',<ref>[https://www.amazon.com/Sustained-Content-Teaching-Academic-Esl/dp/B01F827JAS/ref=sr_1_1 Sustained Content-Based Teaching in Academic ESL/EFL (2000, Houghton-Mifflin)]</ref> for which she also wrote several chapters. She is the author of ''Screening English: Studying Movies for Reading, Writing, and Critical Thinking'' (1997, Pearson Press). Other articles in that field have appeared in ''Language and Education, the Journal of Adolescent and Adult Literacy, Journal of Second Language Writing, and Journal of Basic Writing.''\n\n== Selective bibliography==\n* [https://www.bloomsbury.com/us/mimesis-and-sacrifice-9781350057425/ Mimesis and Sacrifice: Applying Girard's Mimetic Theory Across the Disciplines]\n* [https://books.google.com/books?id=3k1oCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=inauthor:%22Marcia+Pally%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiik4eOpu_SAhWiwlQKHYcUAqYQ6AEIIDAB#v=onepage&q&f=false Commonwealth and Covenant: Economics, Politics, and Theologies of Relationality]\n* [https://books.google.com/books?id=XSIoKQEACAAJ&dq=inauthor:%22Marcia+Pally%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiik4eOpu_SAhWiwlQKHYcUAqYQ6AEIHDAA The New Evangelicals: Expanding the Vision of the Common Good]\n* [https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/3833301376/ref=dbs_a_def_rwt_bibl_vppi_i6 Lob der Kritik]\n* [https://books.google.com/books?id=NWjYAAAAMAAJ&q=inauthor:%22Marcia+Pally%22&dq=inauthor:%22Marcia+Pally%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiik4eOpu_SAhWiwlQKHYcUAqYQ6AEIPDAG Die hintergr\u00fcndige Religion: der Einfluss des Evangelikalismus auf Gewissensfreiheit, Pluralismus und die US-amerikanische Politik]\n* [https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/3866016018/ref=dbs_a_def_rwt_bibl_vppi_i5 Warnung vor dem Freunde Tradition und Zukunft US-amerikanischer Aussenpolitik]\n* [https://archive.org/details/sexsensibilityre00pall?q=%22marcia+pally%22 ''Sex & Sensibility: Reflections on Forbidden Mirrors and the Will to Censor'']\n* [https://www.amazon.com/Sustained-Content-Teaching-Academic-Esl/dp/B01F827JAS/ref=sr_1_1 Sustained Content-teaching]\n\n== See also ==\n* [[LGBT culture in New York City]]\n* [[List of LGBTQ people from New York City]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{official website|https://marciapally.com/about/}}\n* {{YouTube|id=5zfswWojuko|title=Lecture on the book \"The New Evangelicals: Expanding the Vision of the Common\" (Prof. Dr. Marcia Pally)}}\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bUdFdMoRozo&list=PLD0q_7c77seyx_Tj4Djyf7LIiTeqtWgZf Short Conversations on Relationality as a Framework for Public Policy]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yabstRujTso&list=PLD0q_7c77sexY8LUNF6bZMUQULtpsSI9n \"Trump-ed up Solutions\": Will Trump give his voters what he promised?]\n* [https://www.92y.org/archives/rabbi-sacks-dr-carol-gilligan-conversation-marcia-pally Rabbi Lord Jonathan Sacks and Dr. Carol Gilligan in Conversation with Marcia Pally]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bnxewR8Xzz8 ''Our Time'', episode 1 (Marcia Pally at 35:13)]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ri3Utl8DpFc Video - GLAAD: 25 Years of Amplifying Voices, Marcia Pally at GLAAD protest in 1985 (at 0:52)]\n* [https://www.worldcat.org/title/liebeserklarungen-aus-kreuzberg-und-manhattan/oclc/472484287 Liebeserklarungen aus Kreuzberg und Manhattan - Collected columns by Marcia Pally]\n* [http://www.elisarolle.com/ramblings/persistent_voices/particular_voices_7.html Particular Voices: Portraits of Gay and Lesbian Writers by Robert Giard]\n* [https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1197781 Marcia Pally at IMDB]\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pally, Marcia}}\n[[Category:American non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Linguists from the United States]]\n[[Category: Women's rights]]\n[[Category: LGBT rights activists]]\n[[Category: Film critics]]\n[[Category:20th-century births]]\n", "text_old": "\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Marcia Pally\n| image =Marcia Pally press photo.jpg\n| alt = Marcia Pally in her Office\n| caption =Marcia Pally\n| birth_name =\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1951|03|1}}\n| birth_place =New York\n| death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place =\n| nationality =American\n| other_names =\n| parents      = Sidney Pally <br> Nettie Rose Pally\n| relatives    = Iona M. Pally (b. Nov. 28, 1955) (sister)\n| occupation = Professor, Author\n| years_active =\n| known_for =\n| notable_works =Commonwealth and Covenant: Economics, Politics, and Theologies of Relationality / The New Evangelicals: Expanding the Vision of the Common Good\n}}\n\n'''Marcia Deborah Pally''' (born March 1, 1951) is a professor at the [[New York University]] [[Steinhardt School of Culture, Education, and Human Development]] <ref>[https://www.nyu.edu/search.html?search=marcia%20pally&st=people NYU Faculty]</ref>. \n\n==Early life and education==\nMarcia Pally was born in New York on March 1, 1951, one of two daughters of Dr. Sidney Pally (1921-1997), a psychologist with the Veterans Administration,<ref>[https://aad.archives.gov/aad/display-partial-records.jsp?f=4472&mtch=1&q=Pally&cat=all&dt=2158&tf=F National Archives]</ref> <ref>[https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.1467-6494.1955.tb01161.x Article by Dr. Sidney Pally]</ref> and Nettie Rose Pally (n\u00e9e Schachter) (1921-2001). At the time of her birth, Pally's father was completing his [[Doctor of Philosophy | Ph.D.]] at the [[University of Pennsylvania]].\n\nPally was raised in [[Elmhurst, Queens]]. She received her early education at the Solomon Schechter School of Queens,<ref>[https://www.sssq.org/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=1025987&type=d&pREC_ID=1331905 SSSQ Alumni Newsletter]</ref> and has expressed her thanks to her teachers at that school in the \"Acknowledgments\" of several of her books.<ref> See, e.g., Sex & Sensibility, p. iv; The New Evangelicals, p. xx;  Commonwealth and Covenant, p. viii. </ref> Pally completed her high school education at Forest Hills High School,<ref>[http://www.e-yearbook.com/yearbooks/Forest_Hills_High_School_Forester_Yearbook/1968/Page_97.html Forest Hills High School Yearbook]</ref> and the Ivry Prozdor High School <ref>[http://www.jtsa.edu/prozdor-teen-learning Prozdor High School]</ref> of the [[Jewish Theological Seminary of America]]. She earned a [[Bachelor of Science| B.Sc.]] in [[Human Ecology]] from [[Cornell University]] in 1971,<ref> [https://cdsun.library.cornell.edu/cgi-bin/cornell?a=d&d=CDS19710604.1.10 Cornell Sun]</ref> and an [[Master of Fine Arts| M.F.A.]] in choreography <ref>[https://www.wacd.ucla.edu/programs/graduate/choreographic-inquiry UCLA Programs]</ref> from the [[University of California, Los Angeles]].<ref>[https://www.wiko-berlin.de/fellows/fellowfinder/detail/2006-pally-marcia Marcia Pally at Wissenschaftskolleg zu Berliun]</ref> <ref>[https://www.sssq.org/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=1025987&type=d&pREC_ID=1331905 SSSQ Alumni Newsletter]</ref> In 1995, Pally earned a doctorate [[Doctor of Education|(Ed.D.)]] from [[New York University]].<ref>[https://marciapally.com/prof-dr-marcia-pally-c-v/ Marcia Pally CV]</ref>\n\n==Early career==\nFollowing her career as a dancer and choreographer,<ref>https://www.wiko-berlin.de/fileadmin/Jahrbuchberichte/2006/2006_07_Pally_Marcia_Jahrbuchbericht.pdf</ref><ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1979/11/30/archives/events-and-openings-friday-film-music-dance-cabaret-saturday.html Mel Wong Dance Company - New York Times]</ref><ref>[https://www.ejumpcut.org/archive/onlinessays/JC24-25folder/LesbianFilmography.html ''In the Pictures'', Ithaca Video Project, video documentary about lesbian choreographer Marcia Pally in Jump Cut: A Review of Contemporary Media, issue 24/25, p. 90 (March 1981)]</ref> Pally worked as a columnist, and a dance and film critic<ref>[https://www.filmcomment.com/article/willing-sinner-pedro-almodovar/ Marcia Pally in ''Film Comment'']</ref> in Europe<ref>[https://www.arsenal-berlin.de/forumarchiv/forum97/awards.html FIPRESCI jury members]</ref> and the United States,<ref>[https://archive.org/stream/wbaifolioaugsep94wbairich/wbaifolioaugsep94wbairich_djvu.txt Marcia Pally and [[Stuart Klawans]] at WBAI radio]</ref> and as a prominent activist for gay and lesbian rights,<ref>[https://variety.com/2006/scene/markets-festivals/from-rags-to-rich-kudos-1117941139/ Marcia Pally, dance critic for the Native at GLAAD rally, Variety (April 6, 2006)]</ref><ref> Marcia Pally, ''AIDS and the Politics of Despair: Lighting Our Own Funeral Pyre'', The Advocate, issue 436 (Dec. 24, 1985)</ref> and an advocate for women's rights and [[freedom of speech | freedom of expression]].<ref>[https://archive.org/details/isbn_9780415918220/page/256/mode/2up/search/Pally Joan Kennedy Taylor, \"Feminists for Free Expression\" in Jill Nagle (ed.), ''Whores and Other Feminists'', p. 256 (1997)]</ref>\n\nIn 1983, Marcia Pally worked with [[Vito Russo]] in producing<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1197781/ Marcia Pally at IMDB]</ref><ref>[https://archive.org/details/outinalldirectio00witt/page/118/mode/2up/search/Marcia+Pally?q=GLAAD+%22Marcia+Pally%22 Lynn Witt, Sherry Thomas & Eric Marcus (eds.), Out in All Directions, p. 118 (1995)]</ref> and co-hosting ''Our Time'', a groundbreaking television series focused on the gay and lesbian community. The show ran for thirteen episodes on public television station [[WNYC]].<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_O5Vwyj4OOg Marcia Pally co-hosting ''Our Time'', episode 4]</ref> <ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nRFKBuKBGzo Marcia Pally co-hosting ''Our Time'', episode 5]</ref> \n\nIn 1985, Pally became one of the founders,<ref>[https://archive.org/details/alternatechannel00stev/page/254/mode/2up/search/Marcia+Pally?q=GLAAD+%22Marcia+Pally%22 Steven Capsuto, Alternate Channels, p. 254 (2000)]</ref><ref>[https://archive.org/details/longroadtofreedo0000unse/page/290/mode/2up/search/Marcia+Pally?q=GLAAD+%22Marcia+Pally%22 Mark Thompson (ed.), Long Road to Freedom, p. 290 (1994)]</ref> and original board members of [[GLAAD]], the Gay & Lesbian Alliance Against Defamation, an organization formed to protest against homophobic coverage of AIDS in the media,<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ri3Utl8DpFc Marcia Pally representing the Gay & Lesbian Alliance (at 0:52)]</ref> and served as acting chair. Pally's tenure as acting chair was contentious, and led to the resignation of several board members, as well as to criticism of Pally's \"supposed foray into heterosexuality\", and as an assertion that she was unsuitable to hold a position of leadership in the organization due to her alleged refusal to identify as a lesbian. Pally categorically denied the allegations, describing them as \"ludicrous\"<ref>[https://archive.org/details/gaycommunitynews1432gayc/page/2/mode/2up/''Politics or Ego: GLAAD Saga Unravelled'', Gay Community News, p. 3 (March 1-7, 1987)]</ref> Nevertheless, over the course of the 1990s and thereafter, Pally pursued a number of heterosexual relationships that included two aborted engagements, one of which led to a controversy in New York's [[Ansche Chesed]] congregation when Pally demanded and was refused an ''[[aufruf]]'' for her non-Jewish fianc\u00e9.\n\nIn 1992, Pally founded the advocacy group Feminists for Free Expression,<ref>[https://www.boell-bw.de/fileadmin/Heinrich-Boell-Stiftung/2004/04-07BioPally.pdf Marcia Pally bio at Heinrich Boell Stiftung]</ref> <ref> [https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/pdf/10.1002/9781118896877.wbiehs370 Patti Britton, ''Pornography: female directors'']</ref> and served as president of the organization.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1994/07/24/opinion/l-no-censors-needed-on-the-data-highway-758990.html OpEd by Marcia Pally, President FFE, New York Times]</ref> <ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1994/12/11/style/coming-in-from-the-cold-a-fur-lovers-backlash.html Marcia Pally, New York Times]</ref> During that period, Pally published two books on censorship: ''Sense and Censorship: The Vanity of the Bonfires'', and ''Sex & Sensibility: Reflections on Forbidden Mirrors and the Will to Censor''.<ref>[https://archive.org/details/sexsensibilityre00pall?q=%22marcia+pally%22 ''Sex & Sensibility: Reflections on Forbidden Mirrors and the Will to Censor'']</ref>\n\nAfter earning a doctorate [[Doctor of Education|(Ed.D.)]] from [[New York University]]<ref>[https://marciapally.com/prof-dr-marcia-pally-c-v/ Marcia Pally c.v.]</ref> in 1995, Pally embarked upon an academic career.\n\n==Academic Career ==\nProfessor '''Marcia Pally''' teaches at New York University (adjunct),<ref>[http://nyihumanities.org/marcia-pally/ Marcia Pally at New York University]</ref> at Fordham University,<ref>[https://411.fordham.edu/detail.jsp?id=pally Marcia Pally at Fordham University]</ref> and is a regular guest professor at the Theology Faculty of Humboldt University zu Berlin.<ref>[https://www.theologie.hu-berlin.de/de/fakultaet/personen/mitarbeiter/1686853 Marcia Pally at the Theology Faculty of Humboldt University zu Berlin]</ref> Her most recent books are ''Commonwealth and Covenant: Economics, Politics, and Theologies of Relationality'' (Eerdmans, 2016)<ref>[https://www.eerdmans.com/Products/7104/commonwealth-and-covenant.aspx Commonwealth and Covenant: Economics, Politics, and Theologies of Relationality (Eerdmans, 2016)]</ref> and ''The New Evangelicals: Expanding the Vision of the Common Good''<ref>[https://www.eerdmans.com/Products/6640/the-new-evangelicals.aspx The New Evangelicals: Expanding the Vision of the Common Good]</ref> (in German: ''Die neuen Evangelikalen: Freiheitsgewinne durch fromme Politik'').<ref>[https://www.amazon.de/Die-Neuen-Evangelikalen-den-Freiheitsgewinne/dp/3940432938 (Eerdmans, 2011; in German: Die neuen Evangelikalen: Freiheitsgewinne durch fromme Politik, Berlin University Press, 2010)]</ref>. \n\n''Commonwealth and Covenant'' has been selected by the United Nations Committee on Education for Justice \u201cto be distributed in their materials to \u201ceducators, academics, policy-makers, parents, students, teacher training institutes, and curriculum developers throughout the world\u201d and it was nominated for a Grawemeyer Award in religion. \n\nPally's research interests include religion, culture, and politics as well as the intersection of language and culture. During the 1990s, she wrote in critique of government censorship in such works as ''Sense and Censorship'', <ref>https://www.amazon.com/Sense-censorship-bonfires-Marcia-Pally/dp/B0006EZF3M</ref> and ''Sex & Sensibility: Reflections on Forbidden Mirrors and the Will to Censor''<ref>https://www.amazon.com/Sex-Sensibility-Reflections-Forbidden-Mirrors/dp/0880013648</ref> but has stepped away from legal questions in recent years. \n\nPally spoke at the World Economic Forum<ref>[https://www.weforum.org/agenda/2009/12/does-religions-claim-to-truth-lead-to-violence/ Marcia Pally at the World Economic Forum]</ref> in 2010 and has been awarded the prestigious Mercator Guest Professorship (German Research Foundation)<ref>[https://berkleycenter.georgetown.edu/people/marcia-pally Marcia Pally at the Mercator Guest Professorship (German Research Foundation)]</ref> as well as grants from the German Academic Exchange Service, from the Fritz Thyssen Foundation and the Telos/Paul Piccone Institute. In addition, she is the co-recipient of a German Research Foundation grant to compare the political ethics and activism of American and German evangelicals, the only study of its kind.\n\nIn 2007 and 2010, she was a Fellow at the Institute for Advanced Study in Berlin (Wissenschaftskolleg zu Berlin).<ref>[https://www.wiko-berlin.de/fellows/fellowfinder/detail/2006-pally-marcia/ Marcia Pally at the Institute for Advanced Study in Berlin (Wissenschaftskolleg zu Berlin)]</ref>\n\n== Author ==\nIn addition to her academic work, Prof. Pally has been a columnist in the U.S. and Europe for over 30 years, writing for Religion and Ethics, <ref>https://www.abc.net.au/religion/redeeming-populism-the-promise-of-a-liberal-covenanted-republic/10094760</ref> Commonweal,<ref>[https://www.commonwealmagazine.org/-invention-antichrist Marcia Pally at Commonweal]</ref> and Religion News Service,<ref>[http://religionnews.com/author/marciapally/ Marcia Pally at Religion News Service]</ref>  among other periodicals. She has published one opinion piece in The New York Times,<ref>[https://campaignstops.blogs.nytimes.com/author/marcia-pally/ ''The New Evangelicals'', The New York Times (Dec. 9, 2011)]</ref>, and one in The Washington Post,<ref>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/opinions/1992/02/11/porn-didnt-make-him-do-it/e5535a7c-b405-42a4-b595-364cf16fa87f/ ''Porn Didn't Make Him Do It'', Washington Post (February 11, 1992) at A21]</ref> two comments in The Guardian,<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/profile/marcia-pally Marcia Pally at The Guardian]</ref> and columns in Internationale Politik (German Council on Foreign Relations),<ref>[http://www.ipg-journal.de/ipg/autorinnen-und-autoren/autor/ipg-author/detail/Author/marcia-pally/ Marcia Pally at Internationale Politik (German Council on Foreign Relations)]</ref> [[Foreign Policy]],<ref>[https://foreignpolicy.com/2006/11/08/a-familiar-foreign-policy/ Marcia Pally in Foreign Policy]</ref> Die Zeit,<ref>[http://www.zeit.de/autoren/P/Marcia_Pally Marcia Pally at Die Zeit]</ref> Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung, S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung, Tageszeitung,<ref>[https://www.taz.de/!a=Marcia+Pally/ Marcia Pally at Tageszeitung]</ref> Berliner Zeitung,<ref>[http://www.berliner-zeitung.de/action/berliner-zeitung/4484314/search?query=marcia+pally Marcia Pally at Berliner Zeitung]</ref> Frankfurter Rundschau,<ref>[http://www.fr.de/Marcia+Pally~/ Marcia Pally at Frankfurter Rundschau]</ref> Penthouse,<ref> [https://archive.org/details/penthousejuly1996/page/n19/mode/2up/search/+Pally?q=%22MArcia+Pally%22 Marcia Pally,''Film'', Penthouse, p.19 (July 1996)] </ref> [[The Advocate (LGBT magazine)|The Advocate]],<ref>[https://www.biblio.com/book/advocate-issue-429-september-17-1985/d/904100733 ''Lesbian Perspectives (Part Five of Five) - Sorrow and Silk Stockings: The Woeful State of Femme'', The Advocate: The National Gay Newsmagazine (Issue No. 429, September 17, 1985)]</ref> The [[New York Native]],<ref>[https://digital.lib.uh.edu/collection/montrose/item/8226 Gay Press Association Excellence in Editorial and Commentary award to Marcia Pally for \"Fireworks at the Women's Sexuality Conference\" in The New York Native]</ref> [[The Village Voice]],<ref> [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Illusions_(1982_film)#Critical_reception Critical Reception of \"Illusions\"] </ref> [[The Nation]],<ref>[https://www.questia.com/magazine/1G1-3833131/ban-sexism-not-pornography Marcia Pally, Ban Sexism, Not Pornography]</ref> and Vanity Fair, <ref>[https://archive.vanityfair.com/article/1990/12/charles-in-charge Marcia Pally in Vanity Fair]</ref> among other publications.\n\nMarcia Pally has given lectures at many universities and professional associations, among them Oxford, The University of Chicago, Harvard, Columbia University, Telos Institute, Humboldt University (Berlin), The Free University-Berlin, The University of Zurich, Eidgen\u00f6ssische Technische Hochschule, Ruhr University-Bochum, Bielefeld University, The Cato Institute, the Aspen Institute-Berlin.\n\nIn the field of language acquisition, Pally was the editor of ''Sustained Content-Based Teaching in Academic ESL/EFL'',<ref>[https://www.amazon.com/Sustained-Content-Teaching-Academic-Esl/dp/B01F827JAS/ref=sr_1_1 Sustained Content-Based Teaching in Academic ESL/EFL (2000, Houghton-Mifflin)]</ref> for which she also wrote several chapters. She is the author of ''Screening English: Studying Movies for Reading, Writing, and Critical Thinking'' (1997, Pearson Press). Other articles in that field have appeared in ''Language and Education, the Journal of Adolescent and Adult Literacy, Journal of Second Language Writing, and Journal of Basic Writing.''\n\n== Selective bibliography==\n* [https://www.bloomsbury.com/us/mimesis-and-sacrifice-9781350057425/ Mimesis and Sacrifice: Applying Girard's Mimetic Theory Across the Disciplines]\n* [https://books.google.com/books?id=3k1oCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=inauthor:%22Marcia+Pally%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiik4eOpu_SAhWiwlQKHYcUAqYQ6AEIIDAB#v=onepage&q&f=false Commonwealth and Covenant: Economics, Politics, and Theologies of Relationality]\n* [https://books.google.com/books?id=XSIoKQEACAAJ&dq=inauthor:%22Marcia+Pally%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiik4eOpu_SAhWiwlQKHYcUAqYQ6AEIHDAA The New Evangelicals: Expanding the Vision of the Common Good]\n* [https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/3833301376/ref=dbs_a_def_rwt_bibl_vppi_i6 Lob der Kritik]\n* [https://books.google.com/books?id=NWjYAAAAMAAJ&q=inauthor:%22Marcia+Pally%22&dq=inauthor:%22Marcia+Pally%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiik4eOpu_SAhWiwlQKHYcUAqYQ6AEIPDAG Die hintergr\u00fcndige Religion: der Einfluss des Evangelikalismus auf Gewissensfreiheit, Pluralismus und die US-amerikanische Politik]\n* [https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/3866016018/ref=dbs_a_def_rwt_bibl_vppi_i5 Warnung vor dem Freunde Tradition und Zukunft US-amerikanischer Aussenpolitik]\n* [https://archive.org/details/sexsensibilityre00pall?q=%22marcia+pally%22 ''Sex & Sensibility: Reflections on Forbidden Mirrors and the Will to Censor'']\n* [https://www.amazon.com/Sustained-Content-Teaching-Academic-Esl/dp/B01F827JAS/ref=sr_1_1 Sustained Content-teaching]\n\n== See also ==\n* [[LGBT culture in New York City]]\n* [[List of LGBTQ people from New York City]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{official website|https://marciapally.com/about/}}\n* {{YouTube|id=5zfswWojuko|title=Lecture on the book \"The New Evangelicals: Expanding the Vision of the Common\" (Prof. Dr. Marcia Pally)}}\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bUdFdMoRozo&list=PLD0q_7c77seyx_Tj4Djyf7LIiTeqtWgZf Short Conversations on Relationality as a Framework for Public Policy]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yabstRujTso&list=PLD0q_7c77sexY8LUNF6bZMUQULtpsSI9n \"Trump-ed up Solutions\": Will Trump give his voters what he promised?]\n* [https://www.92y.org/archives/rabbi-sacks-dr-carol-gilligan-conversation-marcia-pally Rabbi Lord Jonathan Sacks and Dr. Carol Gilligan in Conversation with Marcia Pally]\n* [